Let's look at some of
the other crazier ones.

00:30:57.540 --> 00:30:59.070
Dental bitewing.

00:30:59.070 --> 00:30:59.640
Yeah.

00:30:59.640 --> 00:31:01.890
So anyone ever bite
down on something

00:31:01.890 --> 00:31:04.980
where you have to get an X-ray
through the side of your mouth?

00:31:04.980 --> 00:31:08.040
Quite negligible amount
of dose, yet they still

00:31:08.040 --> 00:31:10.630
put the lead apron on you.

00:31:10.630 --> 00:31:13.720
I'm guessing that's mostly
for show, because that's

00:31:13.720 --> 00:31:14.920
very, very little dose.

00:31:14.920 --> 00:31:20.350
It's well beyond the 0.1
microsieverts of something

00:31:20.350 --> 00:31:22.000
that counts as nothing.

00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:24.770
But there's not a lot of
dose going into these things.

00:31:24.770 --> 00:31:28.390
Let's see what really does
give you a whole lot of dose.

00:31:28.390 --> 00:31:34.030
10 millisieverts for a CT scan,
or a whole body CT screening.

00:31:34.030 --> 00:31:36.190
That's a pretty
hefty amount of dose.

00:31:36.190 --> 00:31:38.290
Right there with
one procedure you

00:31:38.290 --> 00:31:41.772
may get more than your normal
annual background dose.

00:31:41.772 --> 00:31:43.480
But if you're going
in to look for stuff,

00:31:43.480 --> 00:31:46.270
chances are you need to find
